== Overview == '''Kushitama-hime-no-Mikoto Shrine''' (櫛玉比女命神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社}} located in {{ill|Hirogawa Town|ja|広陵町}}, {{ill|Kitakatsuragi District|ja|北葛城郡}}, {{ill|Nara Prefecture|ja|奈良県}}.
It is listed as a {{ill|Shikinai-sha|ja|式内社}} and was formerly classified as a {{ill|Village Shrine|ja|村社}}. The shrine is situated atop the {{ill|Kushitama-hime Shrine Kofun|ja|櫛玉媛神社古墳}}, an ancient burial mound that remains unexcavated.<ref group="Note">The kofun has not been surveyed.</ref>
== Deity == The enshrined deity is {{ill|Kushitama-hime-no-Mikoto|ja|櫛玉比女命}}.<ref>Hirose District Shrine Registry</ref>
It is said that she is {{ill|Miketsu-hime-no-Mikoto|ja|御炊屋姫命}}, the consort of {{ill|Kushitama Nigihayahi-no-Mikoto|ja|櫛玉饒速日命}}.<ref>Shrine notice board</ref>
== Auxiliary Shrines (Sessha) == * **Benzaiten Shrine** (祭神: {{ill|Ichikishimahime-no-Mikoto|ja|市杵島姫命}})
== Subordinate Shrines (Massha) == * **Combined Shrine of Hakusan Shrine and Kumano Shrine** (祭神: {{ill|Hakusan-hime-no-Mikoto|ja|白山比咩神}} and {{ill|Kumano Daigongen|ja|熊野大権現}}) * **Inari Shrine** (祭神: {{ill|Toyouke Omikami|ja|豊宇気大神}}) * **Amaterasu Shrine** (祭神: {{ill|Amaterasu Omikami|ja|天照皇大神}}) * **Combined Shrine of Kasuga Shrine and Hachiman Shrine** (祭神: {{ill|Hondawake-no-Mikoto|ja|品陀和気命}} and {{ill|Ame-no-Koyane-no-Mikoto|ja|天児屋根命}})
== Access == * A 15-minute walk from {{ill|Hashio Station|ja|箸尾駅}} on the {{ill|Kintetsu Tawaramoto Line|ja|近鉄田原本線}}.
== Notes == {{Reflist|group=Note}}
== References == {{Reflist}}
