== Subordinate Shrines (Massha) == * **Combined Shrine of Hakusan Shrine and Kumano Shrine** (祭神: {{ill|Hakusan-hime-no-Mikoto|ja|白山比咩神|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hakusan-hime-no-Mikoto|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 菊理媛神|1=Kikurihime|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11619891}} and {{ill|Kumano Daigongen|ja|熊野大権現|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano Daigongen|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 熊野権現|1=Kumano Gongen|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11568925}}) * **Inari Shrine** (祭神: {{ill|Toyouke Omikami|ja|豊宇気大神|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyouke Omikami|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}) * **Amaterasu Shrine** (祭神: {{ill|Amaterasu|ja|天照皇大神|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amaterasu Omikami|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 天照大神}}) * **Combined Shrine of Kasuga Shrine and Hachiman Shrine** (祭神: {{ill|Hondawake-no-Mikoto|ja|品陀和気命|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hondawake-no-Mikoto|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 応神天皇|1=Emperor Ōjin|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q317997}} and {{ill|Ame-no-Koyane-no-Mikoto|ja|天児屋根命|1=Ame-no-Koyane|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ame-no-Koyane-no-Mikoto|13=User:Immanuelle/Ame-no-Koyane|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 天児屋命}})
